<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[140,1161,965,1634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,305,996,1020]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis (</emphasis>
male). In the key to the males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[654,767,996,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[654,767,996,1020]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Megaselia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the British Isles (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney" box="[1012,1153,996,1020]" firstAuthor="Disney" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref4577" refString="DISNEY R. H. L. 1989. Scuttle Flies - Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insec ts 10 (8): 1 - 155. ISBN 0 901546 74 7." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to couplets 192, 193, 219 or 222 but its hypopygium differs from all the options. Likewise with 3 subsequently described species. In 
<bibRefCitation author="Borgmeier's" box="[747,969,1057,1081]" firstAuthor="Borgmeier's" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref4427" refString="BORGMEIER T. 1964. Revision of the North American Phorid flies. Part II. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Aphiochaeta (Diptera, Phoridae). Studia Entomologica, Petropolis 7: 257 - 416." type="journal article" year="1964">Borgmeier’s (1964)</bibRefCitation>
key to Nearctic species of Group VII it fails to key out. Likewise for the rest of the world fauna.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[140,1161,965,1634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,245,1119,1143]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Male.</emphasis>
Frons (
<figureCitation box="[327,405,1118,1143]" captionStart="Figs 36–40" captionStartId="8.[139,176,1572,1591]" captionTargetBox="[146,1157,288,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-42@8.[651,1157,680,1060]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 36–40. Megaselia sognensis n. sp. male. 36 – frons; 37 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 38 – postpedicel; 39 – proboscis ventral view; 40 – hypandrium from below." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252457/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) with dense but very fine microtrichia. Cheek with 5 bristles and jowl with 3. Postpedicels, with many small spots but no SPS vesicles (
<figureCitation box="[846,927,1149,1173]" captionStart="Figs 36–40" captionStartId="8.[139,176,1572,1591]" captionTargetBox="[146,1157,288,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-42@8.[651,1157,680,1060]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 36–40. Megaselia sognensis n. sp. male. 36 – frons; 37 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 38 – postpedicel; 39 – proboscis ventral view; 40 – hypandrium from below." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252457/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
), palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[169,249,1180,1204]" captionStart="Figs 36–40" captionStartId="8.[139,176,1572,1591]" captionTargetBox="[146,1157,288,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-42@8.[651,1157,680,1060]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 36–40. Megaselia sognensis n. sp. male. 36 – frons; 37 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 38 – postpedicel; 39 – proboscis ventral view; 40 – hypandrium from below." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252457/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
, the labella large and ventrally as 
<figureCitation box="[623,703,1180,1204]" captionStart="Figs 36–40" captionStartId="8.[139,176,1572,1591]" captionTargetBox="[146,1157,288,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-42@8.[651,1157,680,1060]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 36–40. Megaselia sognensis n. sp. male. 36 – frons; 37 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 38 – postpedicel; 39 – proboscis ventral view; 40 – hypandrium from below." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252457/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
. Thorax brown. 3 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these. Mesopleuron bare. Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal tergites brown with small hairs that are only a little longer at rear of T6 and at most as long as those on epandrium, cerci and proctor, but those on the epandrium more robust than the rest. Anal tube about 1.3 times as long as the dorsal edge of the epandrium. Venter gray with hairs on segments 3–6 that are about as long as those at rear of T6. Hypandrium with posterior lobes vestigial and as 
<figureCitation box="[801,882,1364,1388]" captionStart="Figs 36–40" captionStartId="8.[139,176,1572,1591]" captionTargetBox="[146,1157,288,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-42@8.[651,1157,680,1060]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 36–40. Megaselia sognensis n. sp. male. 36 – frons; 37 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 38 – postpedicel; 39 – proboscis ventral view; 40 – hypandrium from below." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252457/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
. Legs yellowish brown to yellow. Front leg (
<figureCitation box="[350,432,1395,1419]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="9.[140,177,767,786]" captionTargetBox="[146,1137,171,742]" captionTargetId="figure-29@9.[146,652,171,503]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 36–44. Megaselia sognensis n. sp. male. 41 – front leg; 42 – hind femur and tibia; 43 – wing; 44 – haltere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252461" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252461/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
) with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–5 and 5 clearly longer than 4. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.68 times its length. Hairs below basal half of hind femur longer than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1085,1456,1480]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="9.[140,177,767,786]" captionTargetBox="[146,1137,171,742]" captionTargetId="figure-29@9.[146,652,171,503]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 36–44. Megaselia sognensis n. sp. male. 41 – front leg; 42 – hind femur and tibia; 43 – wing; 44 – haltere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252461" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252461/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia (
<figureCitation box="[209,293,1487,1511]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="9.[140,177,767,786]" captionTargetBox="[146,1137,171,742]" captionTargetId="figure-29@9.[146,652,171,503]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 36–44. Megaselia sognensis n. sp. male. 41 – front leg; 42 – hind femur and tibia; 43 – wing; 44 – haltere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252461" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252461/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
with a dozen differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[604,686,1517,1542]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="9.[140,177,767,786]" captionTargetBox="[146,1137,171,742]" captionTargetId="figure-29@9.[146,652,171,503]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 36–44. Megaselia sognensis n. sp. male. 41 – front leg; 42 – hind femur and tibia; 43 – wing; 44 – haltere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252461" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252461/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[703,803,1517,1541]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.96" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="1.96">1.96 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.50. Costal ratios 2.82: 1.83: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[672,771,1548,1572]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
long. Vein 3 hair 
<quantity box="[976,1075,1548,1572]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.04">0.04 mm</quantity>
long. 3 axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity box="[555,654,1579,1603]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.14">0.14 mm</quantity>
long. Vein Sc not reaching R1. Haltere knob pale (
<figureCitation box="[200,283,1609,1634]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="9.[140,177,767,786]" captionTargetBox="[146,1137,171,742]" captionTargetId="figure-29@9.[146,652,171,503]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 36–44. Megaselia sognensis n. sp. male. 41 – front leg; 42 – hind femur and tibia; 43 – wing; 44 – haltere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252461" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252461/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
